{"title_page": "Build-A-Bear Workshop", "text_new": "{{short description|American retail company}}\n{{for|the video game|Build-A-Bear Workshop (video game)}}\n{{multiple issues|\n{{more citations needed|date=May 2018}}\n{{third-party|date=May 2018}}\n{{unreliable sources|date=May 2018}}\n}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2017}}\n{{Infobox company \n| name = Build-A-Bear Workshop, Inc. \n| logo = Buildabear logo.png\n| type = [[public company|Public]]\n| traded_as = {{NYSE|BBW}}<br>[[Russell Microcap Index]] \n| key_people =   Sharon Price John (President, CEO)\n| industry = Retail \n| products = [[Stuffed toy]]s <br> [[Sports|Sports Stuff]]\n| revenue = {{Decrease}} {{USD|358 million|link=yes}} (2017)<ref>{{cite web |title=Income Statement for Build-A-Bear Workshop Inc (BBW) from Morningstar.com |url=http://financials.morningstar.com/income-statement/is.html?t=BBW&region=usa&culture=en-US |website=Morningstar |accessdate=13 July 2018}}</ref>\n| num_employees = ~5,643 (2011) \n| foundation = {{Start date and age|1997|10|26}}<br>[[St. Louis]], [[Missouri]], U.S.\n| founder = [[Maxine Clark]]\n| location = [[Overland, Missouri|Overland]], Missouri, U.S.<ref name=\"new CEO\">{{cite news|title=New Build-A-Bear CEO upbeat on turnaround, future|url=http://www.stltoday.com/business/local/new-build-a-bear-ceo-upbeat-on-turnaround-future/article_422f2109-72bc-526c-a0ee-a2776d0d3f81.html|accessdate=July 31, 2011|work=St. Louis Post-dispatch|date=January 19, 2014}}</ref>\n| homepage = {{url|buildabear.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Build-A-Bear Workshop, Inc.''' is an American retailer headquartered in [[Overland, Missouri]] that sells [[teddy bear]]s and other [[stuffed animal]]s and characters. Customers go through an interactive process in which the stuffed animal of their choice is assembled and tailored to their own preferences during their visit to the store. These preferences include being able to choose from numerous different stuffed animals, along with varying scents, sounds, and outfits.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.engadget.com/2012-09-28-build-a-bears-new-store-concept.html|title=Build-a-bear's new store concept wants you to choose, love, stuff and fluff with high-tech|last=Trew|first=James|website=engadget.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>   Build-A-Bear Workshop is the largest chain that operates in this style. The company's slogan was \"Where Best Friends Are Made\" from 1997-2013 when it was changed to \"The Most Fun You'll Ever Make.\" <ref name=idch>{{cite book|title=Build-A-Bear Workshop Inc. History|url=http://www.fundinguniverse.com/company-histories/build-a-bear-workshop-inc-history/|via=fundinguniverse.com |work=International Directory of Company Histories, Vol.62. St. James Press, 2004 |accessdate=26 October 2017}}</ref> As of April 2019, the company's president/CEO is Sharon Price John.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stltoday.com/business/columns/david-nicklaus/build-a-bear-ceo-gets-no-bonus-but-stock-boosts/article_e99f5a4e-c213-59fc-b566-399b17cc39ed.html|title=Build-A-Bear CEO gets no bonus, but stock boosts her pay to $2.15 million|last=Nicklaus|first=David|website=stltoday.com|language=en|access-date=2019-08-29}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n[[File:Build-A-BearWorkshopVaughanMills.JPG|thumb|A Build-A-Bear Workshop at [[Vaughan Mills]] in Toronto]]\nFormer [[Payless ShoeSource]] president, [[Maxine Clark]], founded Build-A-Bear in 1997.<ref name=\"fbs\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/carminegallo/2015/06/26/build-a-bear-founder-on-the-secret-to-success-big-dreams-and-an-even-bigger-heart/|title=Build-A-Bear Founder On The Secret To Success: Big Dreams And An Even Bigger Heart|last=Gallo|first=Carmine|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2019-08-29}}</ref> Adrienne Weiss Co. was hired to develop the concept.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chicagotribune.com/business/ct-xpm-2011-02-06-ct-biz-0206-healthy-restaurants-20110206-story.html|title=Lyfe Kitchen to enter restaurant mix with healthy eating at its core|last=reporter|first=Emily Bryson York, Tribune|website=chicagotribune.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-02}}</ref> The first store was opened in the Saint Louis Galleria in [[Richmond Heights, Missouri]].<ref name=\"fbs\" /> \n\nIn 1998, Build-A-Bear took investments from Kansas City Equity Partners and Windsor Capital. By the end of the year the company had opened four stores.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/stlouis/stories/2004/12/27/story3.html|title=Clark, Ebsworth cash in on IPO|last=|first=|date=|website=www.bizjournals.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://money.cnn.com/2009/11/02/smallbusiness/how_build_a_bear_got_started.fsb/index.htm|title=How Build-a-Bear invented a bear market - Nov. 3, 2009|website=money.cnn.com|access-date=2020-01-02}}</ref>\n\nWalnut Capital Partners invested $5 million for expansion in 1999. The expansion consisted of stores opened in major cities to bring the chain to 14 stores.{{Citation needed|date=January 2020}} \n\nClark took the company public in 2004.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/stlouis/news/2013/06/04/here-is-how-much-build-a-bears-new.html|title=Here is how much Build-A-Bear's new CEO is making|last=Solomont|first=E.B.|date=June 4, 2013 |work=St. Louis Business Journal |access-date=August 29, 2019}}</ref> \n\nA few Build-A-Bear Workshop locations began testing the \"make-your-own-doll\" concept in early 2004. In November 2004, Clark opened the first Friends 2B Made store with this concept in Robinson near [[Pittsburgh]], [[Pennsylvania]] followed by a location in Columbus, Ohio on November 19, 2004.<ref name=\"pgz\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.post-gazette.com/business/businessnews/2004/11/22/With-holidays-approaching-specialty-dolls-are-where-the-action-is/stories/200411220202|title=With holidays approaching, specialty dolls are where the action is|website=Pittsburgh Post-Gazette|language=en|access-date=2019-08-29}}</ref> By 2006, there were 9 Friends 2B Made stores in operation. By 2009, they were all either shuttered or converted into Build-A-Bear outlets.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/buildabear-idUSBNG2711520080916|title=UPDATE 2-Build-A-Bear to close friends 2B made concept|date=2008-09-16|work=Reuters|access-date=2019-06-06|language=en}}</ref>\n\n[[The Game Factory]] developed and released a [[Build-A-Bear Workshop (video game)|Build-A-Bear Workshop video game]] for the [[Nintendo DS]] platform in November of 2007.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/the-game-factory-ships-build-a-bear-workshop-for-nintendo-ds|title=THE GAME FACTORY SHIPS BUILD-A-BEAR WORKSHOP FOR NINTENDO DS|website=GamesIndustry.biz|language=en|access-date=2020-01-02}}</ref> A Build-A-Bear game for the [[Wii|Nintendo Wii]], subtitled ''A Friend Fur All Seasons'', was released in 2008.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/build-a-bear-workshop--a-friend-fur-all-seasons-teddy-construction-game-due-in-q4|title=Build-A-Bear Workshop: A Friend Fur All Seasons|website=GamesIndustry.biz|language=en|access-date=2020-01-02}}</ref>\n\nBuild-A-Bear released a feature film, available on the [[iPad]] through MoPix, in December 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/build-a-bear-workshop-presents/id483058379?mt=8|title=Build-A-Bear Workshop|publisher=|accessdate=August 17, 2018}}</ref> Cepia, LLC settled a patent and copyright infringement lawsuit over a color-changing bear against BAB in 2013.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/stlouis/morning_call/2013/08/build-a-bear-cepia-settle-patent.html|title=Build-A-Bear, Cepia settle patent lawsuit|last=|first=|date=2013-08-27|work=St. Louis Business Journal|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref> Also in 2013, founder Maxine Clark retired as CEO,<ref name=\"fbs\" /> and Sharon Price John took over the position.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/stlouis/news/2019/03/14/build-a-bear-to-close-up-to-30-stores-reports-loss.html|title=Build-A-Bear to close up to 30 stores, reports loss|last=Kirn|first=Jacob|date=14 March 2019|work=St.Louis Business Journal |access-date=2019-08-29}}</ref> In 2015, a lawsuit sought damages for discriminating against blind people and lack of blind-accessible point-of-sale machines in Build-a-Bear shops.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/stlouis/news/2015/06/03/lawsuit-accuses-build-a-bear-of-discriminating.html|title=Lawsuit accuses Build-A-Bear of discriminating against blind people|last=Unglesbee|first=Ben|date=2015-06-03|work=St. Louis Business Journal|access-date=2019-07-15}}</ref>\n\nOn July 12, 2018, Build-A-Bear held an event in the United Kingdom, United States and Canada where patrons could pay their child's age for a bear.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/money/nation-now/2018/07/12/build-bear-pay-your-age-day-alternative-promo-exists/779658002/|title=Shut out of Build-a-Bear 'Pay Your Age Day'? Try this birthday month deal instead|publisher=|accessdate=August 17, 2018}}</ref> The relatively low price of the [[stuffed animal|stuffed bears]] for younger children attracted massive numbers of people, overwhelming the franchise's stores as well as many [[shopping malls]] in which Build-A-Bear franchises were located. The event prompted a surge in public awareness of the Build-A-Bear brand, according to a subsequent [[YouGov]] poll, nearly all of which was negative.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2018/jul/23/fluffed-it-the-truth-about-build-a-bears-day-of-mayhem|title=Fluffed it! The truth about Build-A-Bear's day of mayhem}}</ref> Sharon Price John, president and CEO, apologized; the company stated that those who had waited in line would receive vouchers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.today.com/parents/build-bear-ceo-sharon-price-john-apologizes-chaotic-pay-your-t133159|title=Build-A-Bear CEO apologizes for chaotic 'pay your age day' promotion|website=TODAY.com|language=en|access-date=2019-07-25}}</ref> \n\nDuring the 2018 holiday season, Build-A-Bear opened six [[Pop-up retail|pop-up]] pilot shops in [[Walmart]] stores. The success of the pilot led to the expansion of Build-A-Bear into a further 25 Walmart locations in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.foxbusiness.com/retail/build-a-bear-survives-the-retail-apocalypse-and-teams-up-with-walmart|title=Build-A-Bear and Walmart team up, fending off retail apocalypse |last=Fernandez |first=Henry |date=2019-06-03 |website=FOXBusiness|language=en-US|access-date=2019-06-06}}</ref>\n\nThe company launched a streaming radio station in October 2018.<ref name=\"slbj\">{{cite news |last1=Konczal |first1=Lea |title=Build-A-Bear targets the big screen with movie production unit, Hallmark Channel movies |url=https://www.bizjournals.com/stlouis/news/2019/08/30/build-a-bear-targets-the-big-screen-with-movie.html |accessdate=September 3, 2019 |work=St. Louis Business Journal |publisher=American City Business Journals |date=August 30, 2019}}</ref> Build-A-Bear Workshop teamed up with [[Warner Music Group#Arts Music|Warner Music Group's Arts Music]] and Warner Chappell Music in July 2019 to partner on a Build-A-Bear music label. Patrick Hughes and Harvey Russell went on board to guide the label.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Cirisano |first1=Tatiana |title=Build-A-Bear Workshop Launches New Record Label With Warner Music Group & Warner Chappell |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/8519250/build-a-bear-workshop-record-label-warner-music-group |accessdate=July 16, 2019 |work=Billboard |date=July 9, 2019}}</ref> \n\nWith an announcement of having secured a deal with [[Sony Pictures Worldwide Acquisitions]] in an August 2019 Q2 earnings report, Build-A-Bear was starting up an in-house production entity, Build-A-Bear Entertainment.<ref name=\"slbj\" /><ref>{{cite news |last1=Whyte |first1=Alexandra |title=Build-A-Bear builds a prodco |url=http://kidscreen.com/2019/08/30/build-a-bear-builds-a-prodco/ |accessdate=September 3, 2019 |work=Kidscreen |publisher=Brunico Communications |date=August 30, 2019}}</ref> The first planned movie is to be a ''The Honey Girls'' movie, which releases songs and music videos on its YouTube channel. CEO Price John also indicated two Christmas movies are in development for the Hallmark Channel with the first to be broadcast winter 2019.<ref name=\"slbj\" />\n\n==Product mix==\nBeyond the built bears, the store carried other merchandise, \"Bearaphenalia,\" to encourage repeat business. These items included candy, greeting cards, jewelry, stationery, stickers, and t-shirts. Also, the stores had a photo booth that converts the pictures into stickers.<ref name=idch/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.buildabear.com Official Website]\n{{Finance links\n| name = Build a Bear Workshop, Inc.\n| symbol = BBW\n| reuters = BBW.N\n| bloomberg = BBW:US\n| sec_cik = BBW\n| yahoo = BBW\n| google = BBW\n}}\n\n{{Teddy bears}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Companies listed on the New York Stock Exchange]]\n[[Category:Companies based in St. Louis County, Missouri]]\n[[Category:Retail companies established in 1997]]\n[[Category:Retail companies of the United States]]\n[[Category:Toy companies of the United States]]\n[[Category:Toy retailers]]\n[[Category:Teddy bear manufacturers]]\n[[Category:1997 establishments in Missouri]]\n[[Category:American companies established in 1997]]\n[[Category:2004 initial public offerings]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in St. Louis County, Missouri]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American retail company}}\n{{for|the video game|Build-A-Bear Workshop (video game)}}\n{{multiple issues|\n{{more citations needed|date=May 2018}}\n{{third-party|date=May 2018}}\n{{unreliable sources|date=May 2018}}\n}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2017}}\n{{Infobox company \n| name = Build-A-Bear Workshop, Inc. \n| logo = Buildabear logo.png\n| type = [